						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1472, Saumya, Śrāvaṇa ba. 6, Wednesday, corresponding to 1549 A.D., August 14.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record the gift [of a pillar] to the temple of Gōpīnātha by Chiṭikoṇḍayya. son of Siṅgarāju of Piḍugurēla.</p>						

						</summary>
